The Vice President, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the Hudson Institute's 2017 Herman Kahn Award Dinner, emphasizing the importance of American leadership in the world. He praised President Donald Trump's efforts to restore American strength and prosperity, including rolling back federal regulations, promoting economic growth, and rebuilding the military. Pence also discussed the administration's stance on various international issues, such as North Korea, ISIS, and Iran. He pledged continued support for Israel and vowed to prevent Iran from acquiring nuclear weapons. Pence concluded his speech by reaffirming the administration's commitment to making America prosperous, strong, and safe.